A 25-year-old University of KwaZulu-Natal (UKZN) student is expected to appear in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court on Monday for the murder of a fellow student. The student was arrested onÂ Saturday morning after he was spotted near smoke in a bushy area, close to the UKZN's Westville campus, at 01:30. READ: Durban student arrested after burnt body of 'close friend' discovered The murdered student, 24-year-old Samkelo Zondi, was reported missing on Wednesday. According to EWN, campus security officials arrested the man after they saw that he emerged from the bushes. On further investigation, a body was found, burning in the bushes. The two students were reportedly close friends.    Sowetan reported that the university said Zondi's body was found in a rugby field near the Westville campus. The publication said UKZN spokesperson Ashton Bodrick said the deceased and accused were acquainted.